  "module": {
    "path": "src/common/structure",
    "name": "structure",
    "purpose": "Owns shared structural utilities for the common crate. channel.rs defines the local mpsc Sender/Receiver aliases, the remoc rch::mpsc NetSender/NetReceiver endpoints and their std::sync::Mutex-guarded SharedNetSender/SharedNetReceiver wrappers, the ChannelError enum, and the build_channel/accept_channel/connect_channel constructors; build_channel builds a local mpsc pair while accept_channel/connect_channel establish a TCP-backed remoc connection whose private connect_socket bootstraps an rch::mpsc channel by exchanging receivers over a base connection handshake.     work_queue.rs defines the generic WorkQueue that tracks working and completed entries behind Arc<Mutex<BTreeMap>> and now exposes a with(key, closure) borrowing accessor that locks working then complete and, when the key is present, runs the closure on a borrowed &V and returns Some(result) (otherwise None), letting callers use a non-Clone value in place (for example to clone an ExecutionRuntime's Sender) without moving it out of the queue. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
    "changeStatus": "unchanged"
  },
